Creator of the heavens and the earth
from nothingness, He has only to say when
He wills a thing, “Be,” and it is. (2- The Cow,117)
In this Ayat careful emphasis should be laid on the words ' ﺑَﺪِﻳﻊُ ﺍﻟﺴَّﻤَﺎﻭَﺍﺕِ ﻭَﺍﻷَﺭْﺽِ ' meaning 'Originator of the heavens and the earth' . the Arabic word ﺑَﺪِﻳﻊُ is used to describe creation from nothing and the Arabic word ﺧﻠﻖ is used to describe creation from something already present. Allama Ibn e Kathir says regarding the word ﺑَﺪِﻳﻊُ :"literally ﺑﺪﻋﺖ means to create something new,make something new" . He explains ﺍﺑﺪﺍﻉ as creation without any previous example and without the use of any other matter or substance.(See Tafsir Ibn e Kathir 1/241)
